## Image Formats

### Required Formats

| Use Case | Format | Fallback |
|----------|--------|----------|
| Photos | WebP | JPEG |
| Graphics/logos | SVG | PNG |
| Icons | SVG | - |
| OG images | JPEG | PNG |
| Favicon | ICO + PNG | - |

### Format Selection

```
Is it a photo? → WebP (with JPEG fallback)
Is it a logo/icon? → SVG
Does it need transparency? → WebP or PNG
Is it for social sharing? → JPEG (1200x630)
```

### Next.js Image Optimization

Next.js automatically serves WebP/AVIF when supported. Use the `<Image>` component:

```tsx
import Image from 'next/image'

<Image
  src="/images/hero/homepage.jpg"  // Source can be JPEG
  alt="Descriptive alt text"
  width={1200}
  height={630}
  priority  // For above-fold images
/>
// Next.js serves WebP/AVIF automatically
```

